Census for 1950 lists Utah population as 688,864 persons.^[https://www2.census.gov/library/publications/decennial/1950/population-volume-1/vol-01-47.pdf]

According a KSL-TV report in June, 2021, over 20,000 Utahns served during the Korean War.

> "More than 20,000 Utah veterans served in the Korean War. Around 12,000 live in the Beehive State now."
